-- Samsung Planning to Grow African Market Share to as Much as 33%, COO Says
-- Kamlesh Bhuckory
-- 2010-07-22T14:32:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/samsung-seeks-to-grow-africa-market-share-to-as-much-as-33-coo-says.html

          
          
             Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd.â€™s sub-
Saharan African unit plans to increase its share of the
electronics market on the continent to as much as 33 percent by
2015 from 20 percent now, Chief Operations Officer George
Ferreira said.  
 The company estimates that demand for electronic products
will grow to as much as $50 billion in 2015 from $10 billion
now, Ferreira said in an interview in Johannesburg today.  
